			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>Uniform Modularization of Workflow Concerns Using Unify</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/NielsJoncheere.html">Niels Joncheere</a>, <a href="../profile/RagnhildVanDerStraeten.html">Ragnhild Van Der Straeten</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_5">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_5</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagM">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The main focus is modularization and composition of crosscutting workflow concerns.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1e.html"><span class="tagL">T1E: Reuse</span></a><ul><li> It aims to enable reuse of workflow concern modules across workflow models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> The approach targets applying concerns across different workflow notations/models, requiring model-to-model adaptation.
</li></ul></li></ul>
